{"id":1140,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/items\/1140","public":true,"featured":false,"added":"2018-12-06T23:15:58+00:00","modified":"2019-10-21T01:56:03+00:00","item_type":null,"collection":{"id":14,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/collections\/14","resource":"collections"},"owner":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/users\/1","resource":"users"},"files":{"count":116,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/files?item=1140","resource":"files"},"tags":[],"element_texts":[{"html":false,"text":"John Montgomery Roberts diary, 1830","element_set":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/1","name":"Dublin Core","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":50,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/50","name":"Title","resource":"elements"}},{"html":true,"text":"The diaries of John M. Roberts primarily focus on his family\u2019s daily farm life in Tazewell County, including routine farm activities, farming expenses and proberty valuations, illnesses and medicinal cures, family births and deaths, local events, and weather conditions. Prior to settlement in Illinois, Roberts was engaged as an apprentice to a lithographic firm in New York City. In the first two volumes he describes the technical aspects of making lithographic plates as well as an earlier trip he made in 1830 to St. Louis and Illinois returning home via New Orleans. The collection of diaries also includes his first wife\u2019s (Mary W. Burhans) account of their trip to Morton in 1831 and his second wife\u2019s (Ann Waters) account of a trip to New England she made in 1859. A few volumes contain miscellaneous sketches of Robert\u2019s home and towns he visited in Illinois. <a href=\"https:\/\/mms.newberry.org\/xml\/xml_files\/RobertsJ.xml\">View collection guide<\/a>.","element_set":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/1","name":"Dublin Core","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":41,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/41","name":"Description","resource":"elements"}},{"html":false,"text":"To transcribe","element_set":{"id":4,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/4","name":"Scripto","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":53,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/53","name":"Status","resource":"elements"}},{"html":false,"text":"100","element_set":{"id":4,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/4","name":"Scripto","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":55,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/55","name":"Percent Completed","resource":"elements"}},{"html":false,"text":"100100","element_set":{"id":4,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/4","name":"Scripto","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":56,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/56","name":"Weight","resource":"elements"}},{"html":false,"text":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/files\/original\/5df39d3982a709ef6d1bb212c134faeb.jpg","element_set":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/1","name":"Dublin Core","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":48,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/48","name":"Source","resource":"elements"}},{"html":false,"text":"Farm and family life in Tazewell County, Illinois.","element_set":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications